reviews.reviewbody:
This is a collaborative reading of Treasure Island from Librivox.org.

This is a great book, and a great reading.  Well worth listening to!

Although I didn't download this, when I was streaming it there were several chapters that sound like the chipmunks.  These are chs 5-6,9-10, 17, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 25-26, 31, and 32.  I tried several times and the problem continued but I'm not sure where to address the issue on this site.

the problem is how the flash player deals with audio file encoding at certain bit rates.

translation: the downloads are fine; the problem is playing in that player.

all newer LibriVox books should not have this problem,,, and i'm surprised this one does.

I was rather disappointed with this reading of Stevenson's classic story. Multiple readers make for a strange listening experience. Some are excellent, others not so good. A better version by a single reader (even if he is from the south of England) is at 
http://www.archive.org/details/treasure_island_ap_librivox

TheBookworm (Manchester, UK)

Once I got over to the uneven recording quality of the voices, I enjoyed listening to this dramatized version of the book. I think the voices were well done and they made the book come to life for me. Well done!
